Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1727,6 +1727,10 @@
 	php_libxml_invalidate_node_list_cache(intern->document);

+	/* Prevent use-after-free by clearing pointers after xinclude processing */
+	intern->ptr = NULL;
+	intern->document = NULL;
+
 	return err;
 }
 '}`
responded: The use-after-free occurs because memory is freed in `dom_perform_xinclude` (via node removal and cache invalidation), but the corresponding `dom_object` is not properly detached from the document or its pointers are not nulled. Later, when `dom_objects_free_storage` is called, it accesses the already-freed memory via `intern->ptr`.

**The correct fix** is to ensure that after `dom_perform_xinclude` (which can free or invalidate the underlying document/node), the `dom_object`'s pointers are set to `NULL` so that the destructor does not attempt to free or access them again.

The best place to do this is at the end of `dom_perform_xinclude`, after the cache invalidation, set `intern->ptr = NULL;` and (optionally) `intern->document = NULL;` to prevent double-free/use-after-free.

Let's prepare the patch.

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/dom/document.c b/ext/dom/document.c
index 5bbe99eb364..259cab8cf39 100644
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1727,6 +1727,10 @@ static int dom_perform_xinclude(xmlDocPtr docp, dom_object *intern, zend_long fl

 	php_libxml_invalidate_node_list_cache(intern->document);

+	/* Prevent use-after-free by clearing pointers after xinclude processing */
+	intern->ptr = NULL;
+	intern->document = NULL;
+
 	return err;
 }

