Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/dom/document.c\n+++ b/ext/dom/document.c\n@@ -1727,6 +1727,18 @@ static int dom_perform_xinclude(xmlDocPtr docp, dom_object *intern, zend_long flags)\n \n     php_libxml_invalidate_node_list_cache(intern->document);\n \n+    /* After removing xinclude nodes, check if intern->ptr points to a freed node and clear it if so */\n+    if (intern->ptr != NULL) {\n+        php_libxml_node_ptr *nodeptr = (php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr;\n+        xmlNodePtr node = nodeptr->node;\n+        if (node != NULL &&\n+            node->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE &&\n+            node->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE &&\n+            node->parent == NULL &&\n+            node != (xmlNodePtr)docp) {\n+            intern->ptr = NULL;\n+        }\n+    }\n \n     return err;\n }\n'}`
responded: The root cause of the use-after-free is that after `php_dom_remove_xinclude_nodes()` is called in `dom_perform_xinclude()`, some nodes (possibly the root or others) are freed, but the `dom_object` (`intern`) may still point to the now-freed node via `intern->ptr`. Later, when the object is destructed, `dom_objects_free_storage()` attempts to access this pointer, leading to a use-after-free.

**Correct Fix:**  
After calling `php_dom_remove_xinclude_nodes()` in `dom_perform_xinclude`, we must check if `intern->ptr` is now pointing to a freed node and, if so, set it to `NULL`. The correct way is to check if the node pointer is no longer in the document tree or is otherwise invalid after xinclude processing.

**Safe Approach:**  
After removing xinclude nodes, if the node referenced by `intern->ptr` is no longer attached to the document (i.e., its `parent` is `NULL` and it's not the document node itself), we should set `intern->ptr` to `NULL`.

Let's implement this logic in `dom_perform_xinclude`.

```diff
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1727,6 +1727,18 @@ static int dom_perform_xinclude(xmlDocPtr docp, dom_object *intern, zend_long flags)

     php_libxml_invalidate_node_list_cache(intern->document);

+    /* After removing xinclude nodes, check if intern->ptr points to a freed node and clear it if so */
+    if (intern->ptr != NULL) {
+        php_libxml_node_ptr *nodeptr = (php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr;
+        xmlNodePtr node = nodeptr->node;
+        if (node != NULL &&
+            node->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE &&
+            node->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE &&
+            node->parent == NULL &&
+            node != (xmlNodePtr)docp) {
+            intern->ptr = NULL;
+        }
+    }

     return err;
 }
```

