Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/dom/document.c\n+++ b/ext/dom/document.c\n@@ -1726,6 +1726,17 @@ static int dom_perform_xinclude(xmlDocPtr docp, dom_object *intern, zend_long flags)\n     }\n \n+    /* After removing xinclude nodes, check if the main dom_object node was removed */\n+    if (intern->ptr != NULL) {\n+        php_libxml_node_ptr *nodeptr = (php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr;\n+        xmlNodePtr node = nodeptr->node;\n+        /* If the node is not the document node and is detached (parent == NULL), it was removed */\n+        if (node != NULL && node->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && node->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE && node->parent == NULL) {\n+            intern->ptr = NULL;\n+        }\n+    }\n+\n     php_libxml_invalidate_node_list_cache(intern->document);\n \n     return err;\n'}`
responded: Here's what we now know from the detailed walk through:

- The use-after-free happens due to one of the inner pointers being freed in `dom_perform_xinclude()` (via `php_dom_remove_xinclude_nodes()/php_dom_free_xinclude_node()->php_libxml_node_free_resource()`). The DOM infrastructure—and particularly `intern->ptr` in the owning `zend_object`—still points to memory that freed xinclude nodes.
- When the request shutdown or other cleanup happens (`dom_objects_free_storage()`), the code assumes `intern->ptr` is still a valid resource, but it may now point to freed memory.

**The correct and minimal fix pattern:**
- After calling `php_dom_remove_xinclude_nodes()` in `dom_perform_xinclude`, check if `intern->ptr` points to a freed node and, if so, set it to NULL.
- The main pitfall is that the DOMDocument object’s main node (`intern->ptr`) may be one of the xinclude nodes removed and freed. We should only clear it if the node it points to is no longer in the document tree, i.e., has been removed/freed.

**How do we check this?**  
If `intern->ptr` exists and its `node` is not present in the tree (or `.parent == NULL` and it is not the root document node), then we can `intern->ptr = NULL`.

We should add this check right after removing xinclude nodes (between lines 1726 and 1728 in `ext/dom/document.c`).

Let's generate the patch.

```diff
--- a/ext/dom/document.c
+++ b/ext/dom/document.c
@@ -1726,6 +1726,17 @@ static int dom_perform_xinclude(xmlDocPtr docp, dom_object *intern, zend_long flags)
     }

+    /* After removing xinclude nodes, check if the main dom_object node was removed */
+    if (intern->ptr != NULL) {
+        php_libxml_node_ptr *nodeptr = (php_libxml_node_ptr *)intern->ptr;
+        xmlNodePtr node = nodeptr->node;
+        /* If the node is not the document node and is detached (parent == NULL), it was removed */
+        if (node != NULL && node->type != XML_DOCUMENT_NODE && node->type != XML_HTML_DOCUMENT_NODE && node->parent == NULL) {
+            intern->ptr = NULL;
+        }
+    }
+
     php_libxml_invalidate_node_list_cache(intern->document);

     return err;
```

